      <text><![CDATA[Finding Real and Imaginary Parts of a Complex Function"]]></text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p></p><p></p><p>Find the real part \(u(x,y)\) and the imaginary part \(v(x,y)\) of the complex function \(f(z) = {@ f_z @}\).</p><p>\(u(x,y)\) = [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&nbsp;</p><p>\(v(x,y)\) = [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]&nbsp;</p><p></p>
<p>[[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked solution</h3>
<br> To decompose a complex number into its real and imaginary parts, we need to  replace \(z\) with \( x + iy \)
<p></p>
<br> Therefore, \( f(z)\) will be;
<br> {@f_z@} =  {@f_xy@}
<br>Â \(f(z) = {@ta1@}+i({@ta2@})\).</p>
<p></p>
<br>From this expression, we can identify the real part \( u(x, y)\) and the imaginary part \(v(x, y)\) as follows:
<br> Real part: \(u(x,y)= {@ta1@}\) 
<br> Imaginary part: \(v(x,y)={@ta2@}\).</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
